SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 199
BY SENATOR BARROW
A RESOLUTION
To commend and congratulate Tami McClure, head coach of the Zachary High School girls
basketball team, for leading the Lady Broncos to the 2024 Division I Non-Select
state championship, for earning The Advocate's "Star of Stars Girls Coach of the
Year" honor, and for her extraordinary contributions to high school athletics in
Louisiana.
WHEREAS, the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana takes great pride in
recognizing outstanding educators and coaches whose leadership, dedication, and
mentorship profoundly shape the lives of young people across the state; and
WHEREAS, Tami McClure guided the Zachary High School girls basketball team
through a storybook 2023-2024 season, culminating in a historic victory over Parkway High
School in the Division I Non-Select state championship game; and
WHEREAS, this championship marked Zachary High School's first girls basketball
state title in ninety-eight years, a milestone that reflects both the team's extraordinary
commitment and Coach McClure's exceptional leadership; and
WHEREAS, Coach McClure, who often refers to her players as "my daughters", has
long emphasized not only athletic excellence but also the development of strong, confident
young women, stating her desire for them "to be amazing women when they leave this
school"; and
WHEREAS, over more than twenty seasons as a high school coach in the Baton
Rouge area, Coach McClure has amassed 621 career victories, including back-to-back
LHSAA Class 4A state championships at St. Michael the Archangel High School in 2008
and 2009; and
WHEREAS, nearly a decade ago, Coach McClure transitioned from the parochial
