school system to Zachary High School, drawn by the school's promise and the challenge of
building a championship-caliber program, urging players and parents alike to "trust the
process"; and
WHEREAS, the Lady Broncos' 2024 championship run was fueled by a renewed
focus following a disappointing quarterfinal loss to Mandeville the previous season, a
moment that Coach McClure identified as a turning point for the team's mindset and
determination; and
WHEREAS, Coach McClure and her assistant coaches demonstrated total
commitment to the program by participating in offseason workouts alongside their players,
modeling the discipline and buy-in they expected from the team; and
WHEREAS, colleagues and former players attest to Coach McClure's exceptional
ability to connect with athletes and adapt to the needs of each team, qualities shaped in part
by her upbringing as the daughter of former Major League Baseball pitcher and
minor-league coach Ken Reynolds; and
WHEREAS, former LHSCA director Eric Held, who coached with McClure at St.
Michael, has praised her early understanding of the demands of coaching and her ability to
relate to players, while former star player and current St. Thomas More coach, Jeanne
Kenney, has lauded McClure's rare talent for adjusting her approach to bring out the best in
every team she leads; and
WHEREAS, Coach McClure's leadership, mentorship, and competitive excellence
have earned her the distinction of being named The Advocate's "2024 Star of Stars Girls
Coach of the Year", a recognition befitting her remarkable achievements and lasting impact
on Louisiana high school athletics; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper for the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana to
honor Coach McClure for her historic season, her championship legacy, and her unwavering
dedication to the young women she coaches.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend and congratulate Tami McClure for leading the Zachary High School
girls basketball team to the 2024 Division I Non-Select state championship and for being
named The Advocate's "Star of Stars Girls Coach of the Year".
